WITH agn_objects AS
  (SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   WHERE p.class_name = 'AGN'
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'),
     band_detections AS
  (SELECT d.oid,
          SUM(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN 1
                  ELSE 0
              END) AS g_band_detections,
          SUM(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN 1
                  ELSE 0
              END) AS r_band_detections,
          STDDEV(CASE
                     WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.magpsf_corr
                     ELSE NULL
                 END) AS g_band_stddev,
          STDDEV(CASE
                     WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.magpsf_corr
                     ELSE NULL
                 END) AS r_band_stddev
   FROM detection d
   GROUP BY d.oid)
SELECT o.*,
       p.class_name,
       p.probability,
       bd.g_band_detections,
       bd.r_band_detections,
       bd.g_band_stddev,
       bd.r_band_stddev
FROM OBJECT o
JOIN agn_objects a ON o.oid = a.oid
JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
AND p.ranking = 1
AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
JOIN band_detections bd ON o.oid = bd.oid
WHERE -- Has r band detections with variability (stddev > 0)
 bd.r_band_detections > 0
  AND bd.r_band_stddev > 0
  AND (-- No g band detections
 bd.g_band_detections = 0
       OR -- Or no significant variability in g band
 bd.g_band_stddev IS NULL
       OR bd.g_band_stddev = 0)
ORDER BY o.oid ASC;

-- Get AGN objects with r-band variability but no g-band detections or variability
WITH agn_objects AS
  (-- Get objects classified as AGN
 SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   WHERE p.class_name = 'AGN'
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'),
     r_band_detections AS
  (-- Get objects with r-band detections
 SELECT DISTINCT d.oid
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.fid = 2 -- r band

     AND d.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM agn_objects)),
     g_band_detections AS
  (-- Get objects with g-band detections
 SELECT DISTINCT d.oid
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.fid = 1 -- g band
),
     r_band_variability AS
  (-- Check for r-band variability by looking at multiple detections
 SELECT d.oid
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.fid = 2 -- r band

   GROUP BY d.oid
   HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
   AND STDDEV(d.magpsf_corr) > 0.1 -- Threshold for variability

   AND d.oid IN
     (SELECT oid
      FROM agn_objects)),
     g_band_variability AS
  (-- Check for g-band variability
 SELECT d.oid
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.fid = 1 -- g band

   GROUP BY d.oid
   HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
   AND STDDEV(d.magpsf_corr) > 0.1 -- Threshold for variability
) -- Final selection

SELECT o.*,
       p.class_name,
       p.probability
FROM OBJECT o
JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
WHERE o.oid IN
    (SELECT oid
     FROM r_band_variability)-- Has r-band variability
AND (o.oid NOT IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM g_band_detections)-- No g-band detections

     OR o.oid NOT IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM g_band_variability)-- No g-band variability
)
  AND p.class_name = 'AGN'
  AND p.ranking = 1
  AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
ORDER BY o.oid ASC;

WITH agn_objects AS
  (-- Step 1: Identify AGN objects with high probability
 SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   WHERE p.class_name = 'AGN'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'),
     filtered_objects AS
  (-- Step 2: Filter objects with sufficient light curve coverage
 SELECT o.oid,
        o.meanra,
        o.meandec,
        o.ndet
   FROM OBJECT o
   INNER JOIN agn_objects a ON o.oid = a.oid
   WHERE o.deltajd >= 365.25),
     band_detections AS
  (-- Step 3: Count detections per band
 SELECT d.oid,
        d.fid,
        COUNT(*) AS det_count
   FROM detection d
   INNER JOIN filtered_objects fo ON d.oid = fo.oid
   GROUP BY d.oid,
            d.fid
   HAVING COUNT(*) >= 20),
     mag_variations AS
  (-- Step 4: Calculate magnitude variations per band
 SELECT d.oid,
        d.fid AS detection_fid,
        MAX(d.magpsf_corr) AS max_mag,
        MIN(d.magpsf_corr) AS min_mag,
        MAX(d.magpsf_corr) - MIN(d.magpsf_corr) AS delta_mag
   FROM detection d
   INNER JOIN band_detections bd ON d.oid = bd.oid
   AND d.fid = bd.fid
   WHERE d.corrected = TRUE
   GROUP BY d.oid,
            d.fid),
     g_band_variations AS
  (-- Objects with g-band variations > 1.0
 SELECT oid
   FROM mag_variations
   WHERE detection_fid = 1
     AND delta_mag > 1.0),
     r_band_variations AS
  (-- Objects with r-band variations > 0.5
 SELECT oid
   FROM mag_variations
   WHERE detection_fid = 2
     AND delta_mag > 0.5) -- Step 6: Final result combining all filters

SELECT fo.oid,
       fo.meanra,
       fo.meandec,
       fo.ndet,
       mv.detection_fid,
       mv.max_mag,
       mv.min_mag,
       mv.delta_mag
FROM filtered_objects fo
INNER JOIN mag_variations mv ON fo.oid = mv.oid
INNER JOIN g_band_variations g ON fo.oid = g.oid
INNER JOIN r_band_variations r ON fo.oid = r.oid
ORDER BY fo.oid,
         mv.detection_fid;

 SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   INNER JOIN OBJECT o ON p.oid = o.oid
   WHERE p.class_name = 'AGN'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier' -- Step 2: Filter objects with sufficient light curve coverage

     AND o.deltajd >= 365.25),
     detections_per_band AS
  (-- Step 3: Identify objects with sufficient detections in at least one band
 SELECT d.oid,
        d.fid,
        COUNT(*) AS det_count
   FROM detection d
   INNER JOIN agn_objects a ON d.oid = a.oid
   GROUP BY d.oid,
            d.fid
   HAVING COUNT(*) >= 20),
     mag_variations AS
  (-- Step 4: Calculate magnitude variations per band
 SELECT d.oid,
        d.fid,
        MAX(d.magpsf_corr) AS max_mag,
        MIN(d.magpsf_corr) AS min_mag,
        MAX(d.magpsf_corr) - MIN(d.magpsf_corr) AS delta_mag
   FROM detection d
   INNER JOIN detections_per_band dpb ON d.oid = dpb.oid
   AND d.fid = dpb.fid
   WHERE d.corrected = TRUE
   GROUP BY d.oid,
            d.fid),
     filtered_objects AS
  (-- Combine objects that meet all criteria
 SELECT DISTINCT mv_g.oid
   FROM mag_variations mv_g
   INNER JOIN mag_variations mv_r ON mv_g.oid = mv_r.oid
   WHERE (mv_g.fid = 1
          AND mv_g.delta_mag > 1.0)
     AND (mv_r.fid = 2
          AND mv_r.delta_mag > 0.5)) -- Final result with all requested information

       o.meanra,
       o.meandec,
       o.ndet,
       mv_g.max_mag AS g_max_mag,
       mv_g.min_mag AS g_min_mag,

       mv_r.min_mag AS r_min_mag,
       mv_r.delta_mag AS r_delta_mag,
       mv_r.fid AS detection_fid
FROM filtered_objects fo
INNER JOIN OBJECT o ON fo.oid = o.oid
INNER JOIN mag_variations mv_g ON fo.oid = mv_g.oid
AND mv_g.fid = 1
INNER JOIN mag_variations mv_r ON fo.oid = mv_r.oid
AND mv_r.fid = 2
ORDER BY o.oid;

SELECT
    sq1.oid, sq1.ndet, sq1.firstmjd,
    sq1.probability as prob_stamp_bogus,
    sq2.probability as prob_lc_transient
FROM
(
SELECT
    object.oid, object.ndet, object.firstmjd,
    probability.class_name,
    probability.probability
FROM
    object INNER JOIN
    probability
    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    ndet > 10
    AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
    AND class_name = 'bogus'
    AND probability > 0.7
    AND classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
) AS sq1
INNER JOIN
(
SELECT
    *
FROM
    probability
WHERE
    classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_top'
    AND class_name = 'Transient'
    AND probability > 0.9
) AS sq2
ON sq1.oid = sq2.oid
ORDER BY sq1.oid
LIMIT 30
